From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 20:05:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: rockchip: Restore RK3399 6.8 PERST GPIO initial state

Armbian kernel narrowing showed that RK3399 PCIe works with the 6.8.11
Rockchip64 edge kernel and fails by 6.12.x with:

    rockchip-pcie f8000000.pcie: PCIe link training gen1 timeout!

The Armbian Rockchip64 PCIe patch stack is semantically unchanged between
the working 6.8 and failing 6.12 patch directories, leaving upstream
Rockchip host-driver changes as the next divergence to test.

One such change is the initial endpoint reset GPIO state.  Linux 6.8
requested the RC endpoint GPIO as GPIOD_OUT_HIGH, then asserted it at the
start of host initialization and released it immediately before link
polling.  Linux 6.12 and newer request it as GPIOD_OUT_LOW, so the endpoint
is already held in reset before the host init sequence begins and the
explicit assertion at host init may no longer produce the same reset pulse.

Restore the 6.8 initial state for RK3399 only.  Keep newer behavior for
other Rockchip PCIe controllers.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@local>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c | 13 ++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip.c
@@ -87,10 +87,17 @@
 	if (err)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, err, "Cannot get the Core resets\n");
 
-	if (rockchip->is_rc)
+	if (rockchip->is_rc) {
+		enum gpiod_flags perst_flags = GPIOD_OUT_LOW;
+
+		/* Preserve the working 6.8 RK3399 reset pulse shape. */
+		if (of_device_is_compatible(node, "rockchip,rk3399-pcie"))
+			perst_flags = GPIOD_OUT_HIGH;
+
 		rockchip->perst_gpio = devm_gpiod_get_optional(dev, "ep",
-							       GPIOD_OUT_LOW);
-	else
+							       perst_flags);
+	} else {
 		rockchip->perst_gpio = devm_gpiod_get_optional(dev, "reset",
 							       GPIOD_IN);
+	}
 	if (IS_ERR(rockchip->perst_gpio))
-- 
